The paper discusses the development of a conversational system for explaining decisions of a predictive model, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also involves the use of machine learning (cs.AI) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) to identify user needs for model explanations. Additionally, the paper analyzes the most common types of questions asked by users, which involves statistical analysis and data exploration (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
